address: 산61-2 Gusan-dong, Eunpyeong-gu, Seoul, South Korea

description: The Korea Furniture Museum, located in Seoul, South Korea, is a professional museum that integrates collection and storage. The museum displays a large number of traditional Korean wooden furniture. In addition, the museum also displays more than 10 old houses in Korea, allowing visitors to see the uses and traditional lifestyles of Korean furniture in real Korean houses.
The beautiful Tea Museum is located in Seoul, South Korea. Here, in addition to learning about the tea culture of various countries, tourists can also taste tea.

address: 177 Imjingak-ro, Munsan-eup, Paju-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea
description: That is the abbreviation of demilitarizedzone, which means demilitarized zone. This means that the two Koreas have drawn a military buffer zone by retreating 2 kilometers from the 38 degrees north latitude in their respective territories. From the Dora Mountain Observatory, you can see the surrounding urban landscape. The Freedom Bridge is where the North and South Korea returned their captives at that time. The iron fence at one end of the bridge is covered with ribbons, and people write their good wishes for reunification on it. The Third Tunnel and Dorasan Railway Station are also the main points of the visit.
